<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[188,1398,311,443]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
The female from 
<collectingCountry box="[402,516,311,337]" name="Honduras" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Honduras</collectingCountry>
is considerably different from the males from 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1177,311,337]" name="Mexico" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Mexico</collectingCountry>
as the description states above. We keep them as a single species until this hypothesis can be further tested with additional material. Specimen voucher UCR_ENT 00004570 was mis-labelled as collected “ 
<quantity box="[1159,1215,381,408]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.437376" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mi" value="4.0">4 mi</quantity>
N of Cardale”, though it should be “ 
<quantity box="[435,489,417,443]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.437376" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="mi" value="4.0">4 mi</quantity>
N of José Cardel” as recorded by other collectors on the same trip.
</paragraph>
